  {
    "udt_union_v0": {
      "doc": "A venue-tagged swap step. Each variant is a FLAT tuple of **registry ids** and\\namounts \\xe2\\x80\\x94 no struct field-names \\xe2\\x80\\x94 so the user-signed payload references pools\\nand tokens by a few-byte `u32` id instead of a 32-byte `Address` each. The\\ncontract resolves the ids to Addresses on-chain from the registry (instance\\nstorage, so it adds no ledger keys to the signed envelope), then expands each\\nstep into the venue's exact call args + authorization tree. This keeps the\\ntransaction small enough for hardware wallets to sign reliably.\\n\\nTuple layouts \\xe2\\x80\\x94 these ARE the wire format the backend encodes (`encodeStep`):\\nAquarius (pool_id, token_in_id, in_idx,  out_idx, amount_in)\\nComet    (pool_id, token_in_id, token_out_id,     amount_in)\\nSushi    (pool_id, token_in_id, zero_for_one, checkpoint, checkpoint_min, slot, amount_in)\\nPhoenix  (pool_id, token_in_id, amount_in)\\nSoroswap (pool_id, token_in_id, zero_for_one, amount_in)\\n\\nOn a chained hop the `amount_in` field is advisory \\xe2\\x80\\x94 the router swaps the\\namount the previous hop ",
      "lib": "",
      "name": "Step",
      "cases": [
        {
          "tuple_v0": {
            "doc": "",
            "name": "Aquarius",
            "type_": [
              {
                "tuple": {
                  "value_types": [
