  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Aggregated, atomic swap with a platform-fee skim.\\n\\n- `user`: the trader and transaction source (single signature).\\n- `asset_in` / `total_amount_in`: pulled from `user` into the contract.\\n- `asset_out` / `min_total_out`: revert unless the contract nets at least\\n`min_total_out` of `asset_out` across all routes.\\n- `routes`: the split \\xe2\\x80\\x94 each route is `(amount_in, path)`: `amount_in` of\\n`asset_in` through its own `path`. `sum(amount_in)` must equal\\n`total_amount_in - fee`. A `path` of more than one `Step` is a chained\\nmulti-hop (A\\xe2\\x86\\x92C\\xe2\\x86\\x92B): each hop after the first swaps exactly what the\\nprevious hop deposited into the router (its `Step.amount_in` is advisory\\nonly), so the intermediate amount never has to be predicted at signing time.\\n\\nSteps reference pools/tokens by **registry id** (compact payload); the ids\\nare resolved to Addresses on-chain. `asset_in`/`asset_out`/`user` stay full\\nAddresses so the submit-side fact derivation + event need no registry.\\n\\n`swap_split_trust` is the identical operation that additio",
      "name": "swap_split",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "user",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "asset_in",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "total_amount_in",
          "type_": "i128"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "asset_out",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "min_total_out",
          "type_": "i128"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "routes",
          "type_": {
            "vec": {
              "element_type": {
                "udt": {
                  "name": "Route"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "fee_ppm_override",
          "type_": {
            "option": {
              "value_type": "u32"
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "result": {
            "ok_type": "i128",
            "error_type": {
              "udt": {
                "name": "SwapError"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  },
