      "doc": "Identical to `swap_split` in args and economics, but delivers each route's FINAL hop\\noutput DIRECTLY to `user` instead of holding it in the router first. This is how a swap\\ninto a RECIPIENT-AUTH token (whose `transfer` calls `to.require_auth()`, e.g. some RWA\\ntokens) settles: the output goes straight to the user, whose source-account signature\\nsatisfies that recipient auth \\xe2\\x80\\x94 the router can't, since it can't pre-authorize an\\nunknown (pool-computed) amount. Every final hop MUST be a venue that can pay a separate\\nrecipient (Sushi/Soroswap); run_step rejects others with `RecipientNotSupported`.\\n`min_total_out` is enforced from the user's output-balance delta. The backend calls this\\nin place of `swap_split` when every route's final hop is Sushi/Soroswap.",
      "name": "swap_split_direct",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "user",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "asset_in",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "total_amount_in",
          "type_": "i128"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "asset_out",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "min_total_out",
          "type_": "i128"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "routes",
          "type_": {
            "vec": {
              "element_type": {
                "udt": {
                  "name": "Route"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "fee_ppm_override",
          "type_": {
            "option": {
              "value_type": "u32"
            }
          }
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "result": {
            "ok_type": "i128",
            "error_type": {
              "udt": {
                "name": "SwapError"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Register the address whose signature authorizes per-swap fee overrides\\n(the backend's referral-discount signer).",
